Re: BSD detection

Bitcointalk

2010-08-12 00:02:06 UTC - [11]Original Post

   [12]Quote from: dkaparis on August 11, 2010, 11:00:16 PM
   There is this piece of code in headers.h:
   #ifdef __WXMAC_OSX__
   #define __WXMAC__ 1
   #define __WXOSX__ 1
   #define __BSD__ 1
   #endif
   #endif
   That code was a bad idea anyway, Iʼm deleting it.  Any Mac code should
   only use __WXMAC_OSX__, not __WXMAC__ or __WXOSX__, and we should stop
   using __BSD__.
   Quote
   #if (defined(__unix__) || defined(unix)) && !defined(USG)
   #include <sys/param.h>
   #endif
   Will that definitely cause BSD to be defined on Mac?
